cuisine: Italian
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Halve the @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely chop @shallot{1}. Halve the @lemon{1} and cut one half into wedges. Slice the @yellow squash{1} into ¼-inch rounds. Toss the squash on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place in the oven for ~{10-15%minutes}, flipping halfway through cooking, until golden brown.

Place your hand on top of the @chicken breasts{12%ounce} and slice into the middle of the meat, parallel to the #cutting board{}. Open the chicken up like a book. Repeat with the remaining chicken breast.

Place the @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} in a #shallow dish{}. Season each chicken breast with @Italian seasoning{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Coat each breast with @sour cream{4%tbsp} and place into the panko to coat on all sides.

Cook the chicken: Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add the chicken to the pan and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} per side, until cooked through.

In a #large bowl{}, combine the chopped shallot, the juice of half the lemon, and a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss in the @arugula{2%ounce} and tomatoes.

Plate and serve: Plate the arugula salad and top with the roasted squash. Thinly slice the chicken and serve on top with a lemon wedge for squeezing. Enjoy!